   its story. The ONLY cleanup you do: if you moved a pre-existing broken
   story aside in step 3 to get the build green, restore it (but if
   restoring it re-breaks the running build, leave it parked and say so —
   a working server the reviewer can click beats a tidy story dir).

6. In your summary, give the reviewer the clickable URL on its own line:
   http://localhost:4400/iframe.html?id=lift-validation-listframe--default&amp;viewMode=story
   plus the Storybook port (4400) and a one-line how-to-stop-it note.

If Storybook is genuinely unavailable, you still owe a live render via
some isolated entry — do not substitute grep and call the lift verified.</story_scaffold>
    <backdrop_note>Wrap the rendered story in a decorator that gives it a non-white backdrop — many DS border tokens resolve to near-white (e.g. \`#FAFAFA\`) and will vanish against a pure-white iframe. A simple \`&lt;div className="min-h-screen bg-[hsl(var(--bg-surface-shallow))]"&gt;\` wrapper is enough when the target codebase's tokens are raw HSL channels; if the token is already a full color, omit the \`hsl()\` wrap.</backdrop_note>
